stateless client-server protocol
client sends request, server responds with message

=request
method
- GET: retrieve data
- POST: submit data 
- PATCH: update data
- PUT: replace data
- DELETE: remove data
- HEAD: GET without response body
- OPTIONS
- CONNECT: tunneling
- TRACE: debugging
URL: scheme://domain.domain:port/path/path?param=value&param=value#fragment
- scheme: protocol (http/https)
- domain: server
- port: service (80/443)
- path: resource
- query: resource parameters
- fragment: resource location
headers
body

=response
status
- 1xx: information
- 2xx: success
- 200: OK
- 201: created
- 202: accepted
- 204: no content
- 3xx: redirect
- 301: moved permanently
- 4xx: client error
- 400: bad request
- 401: unauthorized
- 403: forbidden
- 404: not found
- 405: method not allowed
- 408: request timeout
- 409: conflict
- 413: payload too large
- 429: too many requests
- 5xx: server error
- 502: bad gateway
- 503: service unavailable
- 504: gateway timeout
headers
body

=headers
Accept: media types
Accept-Charset: utf-8
Accept-Encoding
- gzip (lz77)
- deflate (zlib)
- compress (lzw)
Accept-Language: en-US
Authorization
- Basic
Cache-Control
Connection
Content-Encoding
Content-Length
Content-Type
Cookie
Date
Forwarded
From
Host
Origin
Pragma
Prefer
Proxy-Authorization
Range
Referer
Transfer-Encoding: chunked
User-Agent
Upgrade
Via
